This paper discusses the application of full duplex communication in small cell networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure (NI) and information theory (IT). The paper also proposes a scheduling method for interference mitigation, which involves mathematical modeling and optimization, indicating a possible connection to multimedia (MM) and systems and control (SY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the impact of network conditions on the proposed method, which could be relevant to computer networking and communications (COM) sub-category.
